# HTML2Twig

A powerful CLI tool to convert HTML templates to **Twig** (Symfony) or **WordPress PHP** templates.

## Features

- **Asset Conversion**: Automatically converts relative asset paths to framework-specific functions
  - `<img src>` → `{{ asset('images/...') }}` (Twig) or `get_template_directory_uri()` (WordPress)
  - `<link href>` → `{{ asset('css/...') }}`
  - `<script src>` → `{{ asset('js/...') }}`
  - Handles srcset, inline styles with `url()`, favicons, and more

- **Navigation Detection**: Automatically detects navigation menus and converts them to dynamic loops
  - Twig: `{% for item in menu_items %}`
  - WordPress: `wp_nav_menu()` with menu location registration

- **Block Detection**: Identifies common sections and suggests Twig blocks or WordPress template parts
  - Header, footer, sidebar, content areas
  - Repetitive elements that could use loops

- **Layout Inheritance**: Generates templates with `{% extends %}` for Twig

- **Conversion Reports**: Generates detailed `.txt` reports listing all conversions and manual suggestions

- **Batch Processing**: Convert multiple HTML files at once

## Installation

### From PyPI

```bash
pip install html2twig
```

### From Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Piqzaa/HTML-to-Twig.git
cd HTML-to-Twig
pip install -e .
```

### Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- BeautifulSoup4
- lxml
- Click
- Rich

## Usage

### Basic Conversion

```bash
# Convert to Twig
html2twig convert input.html output.html.twig

# Convert with layout inheritance
html2twig convert input.html output.html.twig --layout base

# Convert to WordPress PHP
html2twig convert input.html output.php --wordpress

# Convert to WordPress with custom theme name
html2twig convert input.html output.php --wordpress --theme-name mytheme
```

### Initialize Project Structure

```bash
# Create Symfony Twig structure
html2twig init --symfony

# Create WordPress theme structure
html2twig init --wordpress --theme-name mytheme
```

### Batch Conversion

```bash
# Convert all HTML files in a directory
html2twig batch *.html -o templates/

# Convert multiple specific files
html2twig batch page1.html page2.html page3.html --layout base
```

### Options

| Option | Short | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| `--layout` | `-l` | Base layout to extend (Twig only) |
| `--wordpress` | `-w` | Convert to WordPress PHP instead of Twig |
| `--theme-name` | `-t` | WordPress theme name (default: mytheme) |
| `--no-report` | | Skip generating the conversion report |
| `--verbose` | `-V` | Show detailed conversion information |
| `--output-dir` | `-o` | Output directory for batch conversion |

## Examples

### Input HTML

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <img src="../images/logo.png" alt="Logo">
        <nav>
            <ul class="nav-menu">
                <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <main>
        <h1>Welcome</h1>
    </main>
    <script src="../js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Output Twig (with `--layout base`)

```twig
{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}My Page{% endblock %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset('css/styles.css') }}">
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<header>
    <img src="{{ asset('images/logo.png') }}" alt="Logo">
    <nav>
        <ul class="nav-menu">
            {% for item in menu_items %}
            <li class="{{ item.active ? 'active' : '' }}">
                <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.label }}</a>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
        </ul>
    </nav>
</header>
<main>
    <h1>Welcome</h1>
</main>
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    <script src="{{ asset('js/app.js') }}"></script>
{% endblock %}
```

### Output WordPress PHP (with `--wordpress`)

```php
<?php
/**
 * Template Name: Custom Page Template
 *
 * @package mytheme
 */

get_header();
?>

<header>
    <img src="<?php echo esc_url(get_template_directory_uri() . '/images/logo.png'); ?>" alt="Logo">
    <nav>
        <?php
        wp_nav_menu(array(
            'theme_location' => 'primary',
            'menu_class'     => 'nav-menu',
            'container'      => false,
        ));
        ?>
    </nav>
</header>
<main>
    <h1>Welcome</h1>
</main>

<?php
get_sidebar();
get_footer();
```

## Conversion Report

Each conversion generates a detailed report file (`*_report.txt`) containing:

- Asset conversions performed
- Block suggestions for template structure
- Loop conversions for navigation menus
- Manual review suggestions for complex patterns
- Warnings about potential issues

## Project Structure

### Symfony (after `html2twig init --symfony`)

```
templates/
├── base.html.twig          # Base layout template
└── page/
    └── index.html.twig     # Example page template
```

### WordPress (after `html2twig init --wordpress`)

```
mytheme/
├── style.css               # Theme stylesheet (required)
├── functions.php           # Theme functions
├── header.php              # Header template
├── footer.php              # Footer template
├── index.php               # Main template
├── sidebar.php             # Sidebar template
├── css/                    # CSS directory
├── js/                     # JavaScript directory
├── images/                 # Images directory
├── fonts/                  # Fonts directory
└── template-parts/
    └── content.php         # Content template part
```

